  "text": "Brazelton and Cramer, based on their study, concluded that men provide emotional support to their wives/partners throughout pregnancy and labor and accompany them in the course of preparation for childbirth and in caring for the child [CITATION_1] . This way, they fulfil their role as future fathers. Most surveyed men from both countries accompanied their wives/partners to gynecologist appointments.",
